    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="Latin">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName corresp="#flconcordia"><expan><abbr>Fl</abbr><ex>avia</ex></expan> Concordia</persName> de pr
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/>oprio suo arcam sibi
                    <lb n="3"/>posuit Si quis eam aperi
                    <lb n="4" break="no"/>re voluerit dabit fis
                    <lb n="5" break="no"/>ci viribus <measure xml:id="m1" next="#m2" type="fine" unit="roman_pound" commodity="silver" quantity="10">argen</measure>
                    <lb n="6" break="no"/><measure xml:id="m2" prev="#m1">ti libras decem</measure>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>
                    <persName xml:lang="la">Flavia Concordia</persName> placed a coffin (or sarcophagus) for herself from her own property. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    If anyone wishes to open it, he/she will pay ten Roman pounds of silver to the <term xml:lang="la">fiscus</term> (treasury).
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>
                    The <term xml:lang="la">cognomen</term> <persName xml:lang="la">Concordia</persName> is also attested in an <ref target="http://www.edr-edr.it/edr_programmi/res_complex_comune.php?do=book&amp;id_nr=EDR098047">inscription from the third century A.D., discovered in the <placeName>Persico estate</placeName> in 1893</ref>. According to <ref target="../Bibliography/Master_Bibliography.xml#lettich1994">Lettich</ref>, the use of a toponym as a personal name is not unusual, citing the example of the burial of <persName xml:lang="la">Aurelia Alexandria</persName>, located only a few metres north of the sarcophagus of <persName corresp="#flconcordia" xml:lang="la">Flavia Concordia</persName>.
                </p>
            </div>
